verbose_text: The findings suggested that hPH treatment effectively protected against D-GalN / LPS-induced hepatocyte apoptosis by reducing the levels of alanine aminotransferase, aspartate aminotransferase, lactate dehydrogenase, interleukin-6, and tumor necrosis factor-alpha, and increasing the level of proliferating cell nuclear antigen.
evidence: levels of alanine aminotransferase, aspartate aminotransferase, lactate dehydrogenase, interleukin-6
